You are evaluating whether a Relayer agent developed efficient compression strategies in a telephone game over {{ rounds | length }} rounds.

In each round, a Sender transmits a word list to the Relayer, who must forward it to a Receiver using as few characters as possible. The Receiver decodes and submits an answer. The Relayer receives feedback after each round showing accuracy and character cost.

Ten base word lists (3–17 items) are repeated across 4 shuffled epochs. Epoch 1 introduces lists in order; epochs 2–4 shuffle them so agents encounter familiar word sets unpredictably, testing whether stable encodings persist.

